  "key_findings": {
    "carrier_validity": "Electricity source shares form a natural simplex — 9 fuels sum to total generation. Units are homogeneous (TWh), the sum constraint is physical (total demand), and compositional closure holds. This is a textbook-valid carrier unlike the Planck fake simplex (T6c).",
    "covid_miss_is_diagnostic": "COVID affected electricity DEMAND (volume) more than fuel MIX (composition). At the world level, TV=0.019 vs mean=0.014 — only 1.4× baseline. HUF correctly sees structure, not volume. A demand drop that preserves fuel ratios is invisible to a carrier-based instrument. This is correct instrument behavior, not a failure.",
    "stability_hierarchy": "Trivially stable countries (Bhutan, K_eff=1.0) are monopolies — the T6b negative control already covers this. Russia (K_eff=3.9, mean TV=0.016) is the genuine stability test: four-source mix (gas 45%, nuclear 18%, hydro 17%, coal 17%) that barely moves in 25 years.",
    "domain_comparison": "EMBER sits between Backblaze (tight, R²=0.96 at k=2) and OWID (loose, R²=0.77 at k=4). EMBER: R²=0.87 at k=3. All three domains produce valid but different compression characteristics — consistent with carrier structure, not method artifact."
  },
